---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const jsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfilePage',
  dateModified: new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10),
  mainEntity: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    '@id': 'https://alfredwilliamson.com/about#person',
    name: 'Alfred Williamson',
    url: 'https://alfredwilliamson.com',
    jobTitle: 'Undergraduate, Applied Mathematics',
    affiliation: { '@type': 'CollegeOrUniversity', name: 'Harvard College' },
    nationality: ['Welsh', 'Danish'],
    sameAs: ['https://www.linkedin.com/in/alfred-williamson-137b6020b/'],
    subjectOf: [
      { '@type': 'NewsArticle', url: 'https://www.cnn.com/2025/05/30/us/video/harvard-international-students-visa-trump-digvid', publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'CNN' } },
      { '@type': 'NewsArticle', url: 'https://theharvardpoliticalreview.com/international-student-stories-alfred-williamson/', publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Harvard Political Review' } },
      { '@type': 'NewsArticle', url: 'https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2025/9/7/students-for-freedom-fall-protest/', publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'The Harvard Crimson' } }
    ]
  }
});
---
<Base
  title="About | Alfred Williamson"
  description="About Alfred Williamson: applied mathematics at Harvard College, game theory and geopolitics, research on Russia–China relations, and public advocacy for international students."
  ogType="profile"
  current="about"
>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    I am a second-year student at Harvard College studying applied mathematics. My
    current work sits at the intersection of game theory and geopolitics: how formal
    models of cooperation and defection hold up when the players are states with
    asymmetric power, asymmetric information, and choices that are never simply
    binary. I expect this to become my senior thesis.
  </p>
  <p>
    I conduct research on Russia&rsquo;s growing technological reliance on China with
    Harvard&rsquo;s Research in International Security Studies (RISS), and I work on the
    Global Affairs Program at the Institute of Politics. I co-founded Varsko
    Intelligence, an early-stage project on geopolitical risk. I am half Welsh and
    half Danish, which is one reason the politics of small states next to large ones
    holds my attention.
  </p>
  <p>
    In 2025, when the federal government moved to restrict Harvard&rsquo;s international
    students, I spoke publicly against the university yielding &mdash; at rallies covered by
    the <a href="https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2025/9/7/students-for-freedom-fall-protest/">Harvard Crimson</a>,
    on <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2025/05/30/us/video/harvard-international-students-visa-trump-digvid">CNN</a>,
    and in a <a href="https://theharvardpoliticalreview.com/international-student-stories-alfred-williamson/">Harvard Political Review profile</a>.
    I remain involved in that work.
  </p>
  <p>
    The best way to reach me is email (footer of this page), or
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alfred-williamson-137b6020b/">LinkedIn</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>For journalists</h2>
  <p class="note">
    Alfred Williamson is a second-year undergraduate at Harvard College studying
    applied mathematics, with research interests in game theory and geopolitics. A
    Welsh-Danish international student, he has been a prominent student voice on US
    visa restrictions affecting international students, appearing on CNN and in the
    Harvard Political Review. He can be reached by email at the address in the footer
    of alfredwilliamson.com.
  </p>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={jsonLd} />
</Base>
